race.comment: The big one of the day and GIRLS GIRLS GIRLS (6) looks the one to beat. She settled well back from the inside draw last start before coming home nicely to finish 3.5 lengths away in fourth over 1860m at Avoca. Nicely placed and expected to go well. HOLLY'S STAR (8) won the Manangatang Cup narrowly first up, which was an encouraging return given she's locally owned and this would no doubt have been a target race. Looks primed off the fresh performance and is a key chance down in the weights. PAPAL ARMY (7) has been building toward a race like this, finishing off nicely at Gunbower from well back. Ticks plenty of boxes out to 2000m from a good gate and he's right in the mix.KHOEKHOE (1) won a recent jumpout and looks ready to rumble on the back of that effort. Not to be discounted first-up.
